# TraceTrust: The Agentic Satellite Auditor
**Subtitle:** Verifying Corporate Sustainability through Autonomous Satellite Auditing.

---

## 1. Executive Summary
**TraceTrust** is an agentic AI system designed to solve the **"Transparency Gap"** in corporate carbon accounting. While companies self-report emissions in static PDF reports, there is no automated way to verify these claims against physical reality. TraceTrust uses a multi-agent pipeline to extract facility data from reports, geolocate them, and cross-reference them with real-time satellite emissions data from the **Amazon Sustainability Data Initiative (ASDI)** and **Climate TRACE**.

---

## 2. The "Open & Free" Technical Stack
To ensure the project is 100% open-source and cost-free, the following stack is utilized:

| Component | Tool | Why? |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **LLM (Intelligence)** | **Ollama + Llama 3** | Runs locally; zero API costs; fully open-weights. |
| **Orchestration** | **Phidata / LangGraph** | Open-source frameworks for stateful, multi-agent workflows. |
| **PDF Extraction** | **Unstructured.io** | Industry-standard for layout-aware parsing of complex ESG tables. |
| **Satellite Data** | **ASDI (Sentinel-5P)** | Public S3 buckets on AWS with zero egress costs. |
| **Emissions Data** | **Climate TRACE API** | Free, CC 4.0 data for 744M+ global facilities. |
| **Backend** | **FastAPI** | High-performance Python framework for geospatial processing. |
| **Frontend** | **Next.js + Tailwind** | For a high-fidelity "Mission Control" dashboard. |

